---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";

const contactEmail = siteConfig.contactEmail;
const bookingLink = siteConfig.bookingLink;
const leadMagnetAction = siteConfig.leadMagnetAction;
const leadMagnetFallback = `mailto:${contactEmail}?subject=Send%20me%20the%20BAaaS%20guide`;
const guideAction = leadMagnetAction || leadMagnetFallback;
---

<Layout
  title="BAaaS — Senior business analysis, on subscription"
  description="Retained access to a senior, MBA-level business analyst — 17+ years in banking, software, retail and e-commerce."
  lang="en"
>
  <main>
    <nav class="language-switch" aria-label="Language switcher">
      <a href="/" aria-current="page" data-analytics-click="language_en_current">EN</a>
      <a href="/pl/" data-analytics-click="language_pl">PL</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="hero" data-section-name="Hero" class="section hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">BAaaS</p>
          <h1>Senior business analysis, on subscription.</h1>
          <p class="hero-lead">
            Retained access to a senior, MBA-level business analyst — 17+ years
            in banking, software, retail and e-commerce. For the months you need
            senior firepower, without a full-time hire.
          </p>

          <div class="actions">
            <a
              class="button primary"
              href={bookingLink}
              data-analytics-click="book_call_hero"
              data-analytics-location="hero"
            >
              Book a 30-minute call
            </a>
            <a
              class="text-link"
              href="#guide"
              data-analytics-click="get_guide_hero"
              data-analytics-location="hero"
              data-analytics-asset="unclear_requirements_guide"
            >
              or get the guide → The hidden cost of unclear requirements
            </a>
          </div>

          <p class="cred-line">
            17+ years · Banking · Software · Retail · Regulated finance
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="hero-card" aria-label="BAaaS summary">
          <p class="card-label">Retained senior BA capacity</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Principal-level analysis without a full-time hire</li>
            <li>Documents, workshops and decision support</li>
            <li>Built for delivery, product and portfolio teams</li>
            <li>Monthly subscription, not hourly billing</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="problem" data-section-name="The problem" class="section">
      <div class="container two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
          <h2>You run delivery, portfolio or product work.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="content-stack">
          <p>
            Your people — junior to senior — handle requirements, prioritisation
            and stakeholder calls. But no one senior owns the analysis. Decisions
            stall. Documentation slips. Even strong people whose expertise sits
            elsewhere need a senior sparring partner.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Or you carry capability targets.</strong> You need practical
            business-analysis skill to grow inside the company — not another
            generic training day that leaves nothing behind.
          </p>

          <p>
            Either way, hiring a full-time principal BA is slow, expensive, and
            more than you need every month.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="how-it-works" data-section-name="How it works" class="section muted">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
        <h2>Think subscription, not hourly billing.</h2>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          You hold senior capacity for the month and use it where the gap is.
        </p>

        <div class="steps">
          <article>
            <span>1</span>
            <h3>Pick a tier.</h3>
            <p>
              Core, Pro or Prime — same service, three levels of priority and
              scope.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <span>2</span>
            <h3>Agree the month’s mix.</h3>
            <p>
              Within ~3 retained senior days, we shape the right blend: a
              document, a workshop, on-call advisory, decision support and
              follow-up.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <span>3</span>
            <h3>Keep everything.</h3>
            <p>
              Documents, templates and methods stay inside your company. The
              knowledge does not leave when the month ends.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <p class="wide-note">
          You are paying for retained access and priority — not for hours on a
          clock. Capacity is deliberately limited, so quality stays high. Unused
          time does not roll over; we hold the capacity for you each month.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="included" data-section-name="What's included" class="section">
      <div class="container two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">What’s included</p>
          <h2>Practical senior support, shaped around the month.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="list-card">
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>
              <strong>One analytical or management document each month</strong>,
              on an agreed day — requirements brief, process map, decision
              paper, backlog breakdown, prioritisation framework or workshop
              pack.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>On-call availability</strong> during business hours —
              roughly two days a week.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>An ad hoc 2-hour session within 48 hours</strong>,
              tier-dependent.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>A 4–6 hour session within 7 days</strong>, tier-dependent.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Workshops, facilitation, decision support, templates and
              follow-up</strong> — blended to fit the month and tier.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="not-included" data-section-name="What's not included" class="section muted">
      <div class="container two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">What’s not included</p>
          <h2>Clear boundaries, no surprise expectations.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="list-card">
          <ul class="plain-list">
            <li>Unlimited support or a guaranteed instant turnaround.</li>
            <li>Rollover of unused time.</li>
            <li>
              Large multi-week programmes, or work beyond the monthly capacity.
              These are priced separately.
            </li>
            <li>
              Travel and on-site work. Prime may include a quarterly on-site
              visit; you cover travel and accommodation.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="pricing" data-section-name="Pricing" class="section dark">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
        <h2>Simple monthly subscription. Priced for retained access, not hours.</h2>

        <div class="price-row">
          <article>
            <h3>Core</h3>
            <p class="price">from £5,850 / month + VAT</p>
            <a
              class="button light full"
              href={bookingLink}
              data-analytics-event="select_tier"
              data-analytics-click="select_core"
              data-analytics-tier="core"
              data-analytics-location="pricing"
            >
              Discuss Core
            </a>
          </article>

          <article class="featured">
            <p class="badge">Most chosen</p>
            <h3>Pro</h3>
            <p class="price">from £7,200 / month + VAT</p>
            <a
              class="button light full"
              href={bookingLink}
              data-analytics-event="select_tier"
              data-analytics-click="select_pro"
              data-analytics-tier="pro"
              data-analytics-location="pricing"
            >
              Discuss Pro
            </a>
          </article>

          <article>
            <h3>Prime</h3>
            <p class="price">from £9,500 / month + VAT</p>
            <p>Or scoped to your needs.</p>
            <a
              class="button light full"
              href={bookingLink}
              data-analytics-event="select_tier"
              data-analytics-click="select_prime"
              data-analytics-tier="prime"
              data-analytics-location="pricing"
            >
              Discuss Prime
            </a>
          </article>
        </div>

        <p class="pricing-note">
          Monthly rolling, or annual with a commitment discount. VAT applied
          where relevant. Cross-border B2B is usually handled by reverse charge.
        </p>

        <p class="pricing-note">
          Monthly rolling — no long lock-in. Start with a month and see.
        </p>

        <p class="pricing-note subtle">
          Unused capacity does not roll over — that is the trade for holding
          senior capacity ready for you every month.
        </p>

        <a
          class="button light"
          href={bookingLink}
          data-analytics-click="book_call_pricing"
          data-analytics-location="pricing"
        >
          Book a 30-minute call
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="proof" data-section-name="Who's behind it" class="section">
      <div class="container two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Who’s behind it</p>
          <h2>One senior/principal-level business analyst.</h2>
          <p>
            MBA in Innovation and Data Analysis. 17+ years, including 4+ in
            banking and regulated finance.
          </p>
          <p>
            Comfortable in regulated environments: requirements, audit-trail
            design, documentation quality and decision traceability.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="proof-list">
          <article>
            <h3>DORA regulation</h3>
            <p>
              Translated the DORA regulation into a business-rules document used
              by 35–50 product owners across a tier-1 bank’s software portfolio.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <h3>Regulated telecom platform under M&A</h3>
            <p>
              Principal BA work helped cut sprint spillover of nearly-done
              stories from 10–20% to near zero, and reduced late analytical
              rework by about half.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <h3>KYC/AML solution train</h3>
            <p>
              Coordinated requirements across onboarding, AML monitoring,
              sanctions and PEP screening, and regulatory reporting.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <h3>Retail CLV model</h3>
            <p>
              Built an omnichannel customer-lifetime-value model for a large
              retailer and presented the approach at an IAB meeting.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article>
            <h3>People development</h3>
            <p>
              Helped develop around 46 people and trained roughly 30 more in
              analysis and product practice.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="faq" data-section-name="Questions" class="section muted">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Questions</p>
        <h2>Common questions before a scoping call.</h2>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>Is this just three BA days a month at a day rate?</summary>
            <p>
              No. It is retained access — priority, availability and senior
              delivery across the month — packaged as a subscription. The value
              is reliable senior capacity on demand, not a discounted day rate.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What if we do not use the time one month?</summary>
            <p>
              It does not roll over. You are holding senior capacity that is
              ready when you need it — like a subscription, you pay for access
              within the period, not for every minute used.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you work in our hours?</summary>
            <p>
              Polish working hours overlap almost the entire UK and European
              business day, so you get responsive support in real time — with
              the option to work asynchronously when that suits you better.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do we own the work?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Documents, templates and methods stay with you.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you handle regulated or sensitive work?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes — experience spans regulated banking, KYC/AML, audit-trail
              design and operational-resilience regulation. Clients are kept
              anonymous by default.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you use AI?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes, for accelerated preparation and drafting — always with senior
              review and accountability. On lower tiers this is how delivery
              stays efficient.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="guide" data-section-name="Guide download" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="guide-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">Not ready to talk?</p>
          <h2>Take the thinking with you.</h2>
          <p>
            Get the guide — <em>The hidden cost of unclear requirements</em> —
            plus a one-page Definition of Ready checklist.
          </p>

          <form
            class="lead-form"
            method="POST"
            action={guideAction}
            data-lead-form
            data-analytics-asset="unclear_requirements_guide"
            data-analytics-location="guide"
          >
            <input
              type="email"
              name="email"
              autocomplete="email"
              placeholder="your email"
              aria-label="Email address"
              required
            />
            <button class="button primary" type="submit">Send it to me</button>
          </form>

          <p class="form-note">
            No spam. One useful note a month, unsubscribe anytime.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" data-section-name="Ready to talk?" class="section final-cta muted">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Ready to talk?</p>
        <h2>A 30-minute scoping call is the quickest way to see if this fits.</h2>
        <p>We will look at where the gap is and which tier makes sense.</p>

        <div class="actions">
          <a
            class="button primary"
            href={bookingLink}
            data-analytics-click="book_call_footer"
            data-analytics-location="footer"
          >
            Book a 30-minute call
          </a>

          <a
            class="button secondary"
            href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}
            data-analytics-click="email_contact_footer"
            data-analytics-location="footer"
          >
            Email {contactEmail}
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
